## Task Overview

Create the detection.rs module with comprehensive logic to determine whether the current
execution environment is an AI coding agent (which needs plain text) or a human terminal
(which can display rich output).

## Why This Matters

AI coding agents like Claude Code, Codex, and Cursor:
- Parse stdout/stderr to understand program output
- Cannot meaningfully process ANSI escape codes
- Need structured, predictable text formats
- Often run in non-TTY environments

If we show them rich output with box characters and colors, their parsing breaks.
We MUST detect these environments and fall back to plain text.

